# Git commits — no Cursor co-author

When creating commits in this repository (via terminal or instructions to the user):

- Do **not** add `Co-authored-by: Cursor`, `Co-authored-by: cursoragent@cursor.com`, or any similar Cursor attribution trailer to commit messages.
- Use a normal subject and body only.

The repo can strip these lines automatically if hooks are enabled: `git config core.hooksPath githooks` (from the repo root).

